definition.value: A methylbutyric acid comprising a butyric acid core carrying a 2-methyl substituent. Produced from amino acid leucine during nutrient starvation in bacteria.
A 3-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is acetoacetic acid which is substituted at position 2 by a methyl group.

A racemate composed of equimolar amounts of exo-(+)- and exo-(-)-cinmethylin. It is a soil-applied preemergence herbicide developed by Shell Chemical company and used to control annual grasses such as green foxtail and bamyardgrass, it also supresses the growth of several annual broadleaf weeds such as prickly sida and velvetleaf.
A beta-amino acid that is butyric acid which is substituted by an amino group at position 3.
A 3-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is isovaleric acid substituted at position 3 by a hydroxy group. Used as indicator of biotin deficiency.

An 8-carbon, beta-hydroxy fatty acid which may be a marker for primary defects of beta-hydroxy fatty acid metabolism. Repeating unit of poly(3-hydroxyoctanoic acid), a biopolymer used by numerous bacterial species as carbon and energy reserves.
The (R)-enantiomer of 3-hydroxyoctanoic acid; an important building block in the biomedical and pharmaceutical fields.
A 1-pyrroline-5-carboxylic acid in which the chiral centre has S configuration.
A branched-chain saturated fatty acid consisting of octanoic acid carrying a 7-methyl group.
